<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1831,2038]" lastBlockId="13.[151,1436,151,357]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="464" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,1975,2001]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Habitat.</emphasis>
This species is usually found along the vegetated margins of streams and rivers in standing or slowmoving water and in flood-prone areas of streams in shaded areas (
<bibRefCitation author="Torres, P. L. M. &amp; Mazzucconi, S. A. &amp; Michat, M. C." box="[892,1092,2011,2038]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" pagination="127 - 153" refId="ref58586" refString="Torres, P. L. M., Mazzucconi, S. A. &amp; Michat, M. C. (2007) Los coleopteros y heteropteros acuaticos del Parque Nacional El Palmar (Provincia de Entre Rios, Argentina): lista faunistica, diversidad y distribucion. Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 66, 127 - 153." type="journal article" year="2007">
Torres 
<emphasis box="[972,1027,2011,2037]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Rodrigues, J. M. D. S. &amp; Nery, L. &amp; Rodrigues, H. D. D. &amp; Moreira, F. F. F." box="[1103,1360,2011,2038]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" pagination="103 - 159" refId="ref57526" refString="Rodrigues, J. M. D. S., Nery, L., Rodrigues, H. D. D. &amp; Moreira, F. F. F. (2021 b) Survey of the semiaquatic bugs (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Gerromorpha) from Alagoas and Sergipe, Northeast Brazil. Zootaxa, 4958 (1), 103 - 159. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4958.1.9" type="journal article" year="2021">
Rodrigues 
<emphasis box="[1225,1280,2011,2037]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">et al.</emphasis>
2021b
</bibRefCitation>
), but it has also been collected where vegetation was absent in unshaded areas (
<bibRefCitation author="Torres, P. L. M. &amp; Mazzucconi, S. A. &amp; Michat, M. C." box="[961,1165,151,177]" pageId="13" pageNumber="464" pagination="127 - 153" refId="ref58586" refString="Torres, P. L. M., Mazzucconi, S. A. &amp; Michat, M. C. (2007) Los coleopteros y heteropteros acuaticos del Parque Nacional El Palmar (Provincia de Entre Rios, Argentina): lista faunistica, diversidad y distribucion. Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 66, 127 - 153." type="journal article" year="2007">
Torres 
<emphasis box="[1041,1098,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="464">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
), and in pools along dry streams (
<bibRefCitation author="Dias-Silva, K. &amp; Moreira, F. F. F. &amp; Giehl, N. F. S. &amp; Nobrega, C. C. &amp; Cabette, H. S. R." box="[251,502,187,213]" pageId="13" pageNumber="464" pagination="201 - 235" refId="ref48777" refString="Dias-Silva, K., Moreira, F. F. F., Giehl, N. F. S., Nobrega, C. C. &amp; Cabette, H. S. R. (2013) Gerromorpha (Hemiptera: Heteroptera) of eastern Mato Grosso State, Brazil: checklist, new records, and species distribution modeling. Zootaxa, 3736 (3), 201 - 235. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3736.3.1" type="journal article" year="2013">
Dias-Silva 
<emphasis box="[378,435,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="464">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). It has also been found in puddles and ponds (
<bibRefCitation author="Pereira, D. L. V. &amp; Melo, A. L." box="[1025,1269,187,213]" pageId="13" pageNumber="464" pagination="643 - 648" refId="ref55645" refString="Pereira, D. L. V. &amp; Melo, A. L. (2007) Aquatic and semiaquatic Heteroptera (Insecta) from Pitinga, Amazonas, Brazil. Acta Amazonica, 37, 643 - 648. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0044 - 59672007000400021" type="journal article" year="2007">Pereira &amp; Melo 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="13" pageNumber="464">At the INR, specimens were collected in standing or slow-moving water along the margins without aquatic vegetation of Pay Ubre Chico Stream and Pay Ubre Grande Stream, in shaded places.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="464" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="13" pageNumber="464">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,295,321]" pageId="13" pageNumber="464">Remarks.</emphasis>
The collection of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Drake &amp; Harris" authorityYear="1933" box="[521,670,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Microvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="464" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venustatis">
<emphasis box="[521,670,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="464">M. venustatis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from INR represents the first record from 
<collectingRegion box="[1149,1376,295,321]" country="Argentina" name="Corrientes" pageId="13" pageNumber="464">Corrientes Province</collectingRegion>
. This species was collected together with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Drake" authorityYear="1920" box="[544,635,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Microvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="464" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hinei">
<emphasis box="[544,635,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="464">M. hinei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[687,813,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="464">
<taxonomicName authorityName="White" authorityYear="1879" box="[687,809,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Microvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="464" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimula">M. mimula</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
